  "body": "Is there any code convention/reason for not using [`template literals`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Template_literals) consistently?\n\n**using template literals:**\n\n```\n$ git grep -e \"\\${\" | grep '^src' | egrep -v 'test|__tests__|vendor'\nsrc/isomorphic/classic/element/ReactElementValidator.js:      addendum = ` Check the top-level render call using <${parentName}>.`;\n...\n```\n\n**using string concatenation:**\n\n```\n$ git grep -e \"' + \" -e \" + '\" | grep '^src' | egrep -v 'test|__tests__|vendor'\nsrc/addons/transitions/ReactCSSTransitionGroup.js:  var timeoutPropName = 'transition' + transitionType + 'Timeout';\n...\n```\n\nThere are couple of more occurrences like\n[`return prefix + key.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + key.substring(1);` ](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/src/renderers/dom/shared/CSSProperty.js#L63)\n",
